    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 420153,
      "reputation" : 745,
      "user_id" : 797707,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/77df0303b49028b50a1e976b09ceb3e4?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Peter Jamieson",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/797707/peter-jamieson"
    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 7,
    "last_activity_date" : 1328112603,
    "creation_date" : 1328112603,
    "answer_id" : 9099155,
    "question_id" : 9098755,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>So the API is not returning a Vector of Strings but a Vector of String[].</p>\n\n<p>You should be able to iterate through the vector and then, for each element, loop through the array.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Iterator&lt;String[]&gt; iter = dataVector.iterator();\n\nwhile( iter.hasNext()) {\n    String[] array = iter.next();\n    for(int i=0; i &lt; array.length; i++)\n    {\n       System.out.println(i + \": \" + array[i]);\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 26137201,
      "reputation" : 178,
      "user_id" : 19827057,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/eAPUxDRv.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "mariya cherian",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/19827057/mariya-cherian"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1764304234,
    "creation_date" : 1764304234,
    "answer_id" : 79832245,
    "question_id" : 9098755,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>From your question you didn't specify the <code>dataAPI.getReturnVector()</code> ,From this error, the element is look like <strong>String[] not String object</strong>.To confirm this checked the Vector&lt;?&gt; dataVector as String and String[].</p>\n<pre><code>\n    Vector&lt;String[]&gt; dataVector = new Vector&lt;&gt;();\n    dataVector.add(new String[] { &quot;A&quot;, &quot;B&quot; });\n    Iterator&lt;?&gt; iter = dataVector.iterator();\n    while (iter.hasNext())\n    {\n      System.out.println(iter.next());\n    }\n</code></pre>\n<p>with this getting the error<br />\n<code>`[Ljava.lang.String;@15db9742`</code></p>\n<p>but with</p>\n<pre><code>\n    Vector&lt;String&gt; dataVector = new Vector&lt;&gt;();\n    dataVector.add(&quot;hello&quot;);\n    Iterator&lt;?&gt; iter = dataVector.iterator();\n    while (iter.hasNext())\n    {\n      System.out.println(iter.next());\n    }\n</code></pre>\n<p>getting the output.you can find the type of the output by</p>\n<pre><code>\n    Iterator&lt;?&gt; iter = dataVector.iterator();\n    Object o = iter.next();\n    System.out.println(o.getClass());\n</code></pre>\n<p>So from this you are getting String[] not String. That is why you got that Exception.Finally you can use in the following way</p>\n<pre><code>\n    Iterator&lt;?&gt; iter = dataVector.iterator();\n    while (iter.hasNext())\n    {\n      String[] arr = (String[]) iter.next();\n      for (String s : arr)\n      {\n        System.out.println(s);\n      }\n    }\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
